<figure class="viz geometry-viz" aria-labelledby="jspace-geometry-title">
  <figcaption id="jspace-geometry-title">
    <strong>Sparse J-space is a union of nonnegative cones</strong>
    <span>Each active set selects a different cone inside the residual stream.</span>
  </figcaption>

  <div class="geometry">
    <div class="field" role="img" aria-label="Schematic projection of several sparse cones">
      <span class="origin">origin</span>
      <div class="cone cone-a"><i></i><b>active set A</b></div>
      <div class="cone cone-b"><i></i><b>active set B</b></div>
      <div class="cone cone-c"><i></i><b>active set C</b></div>
    </div>

    <div class="reading">
      <section>
        <span>Inside one cone</span>
        <strong>Nonnegative coefficients</strong>
        <small>The activation combines only the vectors in its active set.</small>
      </section>
      <section>
        <span>Across cones</span>
        <strong>Active vectors can change</strong>
        <small>The full set is not one low-dimensional linear plane.</small>
      </section>
      <section>
        <span>Outside the set</span>
        <strong>Residual computation remains</strong>
        <small>J-space is a partial interface, not a complete activation model.</small>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="decomposition">
    <span>activation</span>
    <i aria-hidden="true">=</i>
    <strong>sparse J-space component</strong>
    <i aria-hidden="true">+</i>
    <strong>residual outside J-space</strong>
  </div>
  <p>Schematic projection. Position and area do not encode measured variance.</p>
</figure>

